    "memory_budget": {
        "_comment": [
            "MEMORY BUDGET FORMULA",
            "─────────────────────",
            "Total memory per agent:",
            "  M_agent = M_weights + M_kvcache",
            "",
            "Weights (Q4 quantization approximation):",
            "  M_weights ≈ 0.5 GB × B_params",
            "  e.g. 70B model → ~35 GB;  32B → ~16 GB;  7B → ~3.5 GB",
            "",
            "KV cache:",
            "  M_kvcache = (2 × n_layers × n_kv_heads × d_head × ctx_len × 2 bytes) / 1e9",
            "  Simplified rule of thumb:",
            "    M_kvcache_GB ≈ (n_layers × n_kv_heads × d_head × ctx_len) / 268_000_000",
            "",
            "Hardware agent capacity:",
            "  N_hw = floor(M_available / M_agent)",
            "",
            "FOO minimum agent count (Byzantine consensus):",
            "  N_foo(p, C) = ceil( log(1 - C) / log(p) )",
            "  where p = per-agent invalidation rate, C = desired confidence",
            "  e.g. p=0.20, C=0.99 → N_foo = 5",
            "",
            "Agent Feasibility Score (AFS):",
            "  AFS = N_hw / N_foo",
            "  AFS >= 1.0 required for a valid FOO consensus round.",
            "  AFS < 1.0 means: reduce context window, downsize model,",
            "  or relax confidence target C.",
            "",
            "Context window guidance:",
            "  8K   → fast agents, many simultaneous, less document grounding",
            "  32K  → balanced; recommended for MAX consensus tasks",
            "  128K → deep document analysis; 1-2 agents max on Spark"
        ],
